"{'model': 'mistral:latest', 'response': '\"{ \\\\\"title\\\\\": \\\\\"Reversed Words Checker (Hard)\\\\\", \\\\\"description\\\\\": \\\\\"Write a function `reversed_words` that checks if a given sentence, where each word is separated by a single space, reads the same forwards and backwards when the individual words are reversed. The sentence may contain letters, numbers, spaces, punctuation, and special characters.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n#### Function Signature\\\\\\\\n```python\\\\\\\\ndef reversed_words(s: str) -> bool:\\\\\\\\n```\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n#### Input\\\\\\\\n- `s` (str): A sentence where each word is separated by a single space.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n#### Output\\\\\\\\n- Returns `True` if the input sentence reads the same forwards and backwards when the individual words are reversed, `False` otherwise.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\", \\\\\"code\\\\\": \\\\\"def reversed_words(s: str) -> bool:\\\\\\\\n    # Split the string into words\\\\\\\\n    words = s.split()\\\\\\\\n    # Reverse each word and join them back together\\\\\\\\n    reversed_words = \\' \\'.join(word[::-1] for word in words)\\\\\\\\n    # Check if the original sentence is equal to the reversed sentence\\\\\\\\n    return s == reversed_words\\\\\", \\\\\"tests\\\\\": [\\\\\"assert reversed_words(\\'A man, a plan, a canal, Panama\\') == False\\\\\", \\\\\"assert reversed_words(\\'racecar racecar\\') == True\\\\\", \\\\\"assert reversed_words(\\'hello world\\') == False\\\\\", \\\\\"assert reversed_words(\\'No \\\\\\\\\\'x\\\\\\\\\\' in Nixon\\') == False\\\\\"] }\"'}"